**Nmap**
stealth scan -> map -sS -T4 -p- -Pn ip
Udp scan first 100 ports -> nmap -sU -T4 -p1-100 -Pn ip
Udp scan most used 100 ports -> nmap -sU -T4 --top-ports=100 -Pn ip
web vhost scan -> nmap -p80 --script http-vhosts --script-args 'http-vhosts.domain=example.com,http-vhosts.file=vhosts.txt' <target> 

ipsec scan ->sudo nmap -sC -sV -vv -oA [ip] 
{
 -sV -> version detection
 -sC -> default enum script 
  -sS -> stealth scan only syn packet
  -sU -> udp scan
  -vv -> very verbose 
  -oA -> output all {as file !!!!}
  
 }



